                    RM_PARAM flags may vary across customers based on
                    their specific business requirements. Any
                    non-standard settings should be handled through
                    configurable parameters instead of hard-coded
                    changes.</p>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>Three-level approval: how many levels
                      active? Who approves? Same across all customers?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong><br>
                    Three-level approval is not applicable across all
                    customers. It varies from customer to customer and
                    should be configurable through parameters rather
                    than procedure-level changes.<br>
                    For corporate customers:</p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <p>First level: RM Department Head</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>Second level: Plant Head</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>Third level: Management</p>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>2. SP_PRToPO_RMI/Filter: any known SP
                      behaviour differences or bugs at customer sites?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong><br>
                    In PO print, PR Number and PR Date should be
                    displayed only when a PR is selected. They should
                    not appear if no PR is selected.</p>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>3. Most common support calls for PO screen?
                      Data errors SPINRISE must prevent?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong></p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <p>GST rate % sometimes varies from the Variety
                        setup.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>GST rate % should be mandatory and must be
                        loaded from the Variety Master. For import
                        transactions, GST applicability should be
                        controlled through a parameter, and the GST type
                        should be selected manually based on that.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>Validation is required for Local, Interstate,
                        and Import types based on the supplier’s state.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>Based on Arrival Type and UoM, proper Rate/Unit
                        validation is required. For example, users
                        sometimes select “Candy” rate but enter rate per
                        KG, leading to data inconsistencies.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>Proper tab focus sequence is required.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>Navigation not working properly.</li>
                    <li>
                      <p>In lookup fields, if a correct code is entered,
                        the lookup window should not reopen.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>If UoM is “Candy,” Arrival Type should default
                        to “Pack-wise.” If UoM is “KGS,” Arrival Type
                        should automatically default to “KGS.”</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <p>If tax calculation is set as “Individual,”
                        there is no issue. However, when set as “Common
                        for all” across multiple varieties, calculation
                        errors may occur and should be handled.</p>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>Year-end: can PO be raised after close?
                      Known year-end issues handled manually?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong><br>
                    No, PO cannot be raised after year-end closure.</p>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>Deletion: cases where VB6 allowed deletion
                      that SPINRISE should not?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong><br>
                    PO should not be allowed to be deleted once even the
                    first level of approval is completed.</p>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>Backdate parameter across live customers?
                      Stricter controls in SPINRISE?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong><br>
                    Backdated entry provision is not required in
                    SPINRISE.</p>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>Delete Reason: is DelReasonCode written to
                      RM_Trans_Log.DelReason or a separate table?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong><br>
                    Maintaining the delete reason in the log table is
                    sufficient.</p>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>Cry_RMIPO_JAT_NEW: what changed vs
                      Cry_RMI_PO_ALL? Any report layout/data
                      differences?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong><br>
                    No changes. Both reports have the same layout and
                    data.</p>
                  <hr>
                  <p><strong>With-Sample mode (wosample=Y): how often
                      used? Which customers? Default or optional in
                      SPINRISE?</strong></p>
                  <p><strong>IST Reply:</strong><br>
                    This is optional and used only by specific customers
                    as required.</p>
                  <hr>
                  <p>Regards,<br>
                    P.B. Saravanan</p>
